</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,151,1257]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1158,1184]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Comments.</emphasis>
Chromatic variation of adults has been observed in different collections from the 
<typeStatus box="[1289,1337,1159,1185]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
locality. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,315,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gregori">
<emphasis box="[151,315,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Druon gregori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually has a completely black head and darkened coxae and proximal half of femora. The variant specimens have rusty brown genae and lower face, and amber legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
